article.headline: North Texas 78, Louisiana-Lafayette 64
article.story: LAFAYETTE, La. -- Tristan Thompson scored a game-high 27 points to lead North Texas to a 78-64 victory over Louisiana-Lafayette on Thursday night. Thompson shot 11 of 15, and drilled five 3-pointers for the Mean Green (8-2, 1-0 Sun Belt Conference). Eric Tramiel contributed with 10 points and nine rebounds. The Ragin' Cajuns (4-5, 0-1) were paced by Travis Bureau, who scored 14 points. Lamar Roberson had 12, and Ryan McCoy added 11. The Mean Green went on a 12-4 run with 9:17 remaining in the first half, thanks to four consecutive 3-pointers: two from Thompson and one each by Collin Dennis and Adam McCoy. North Texas maintained a 34-28 lead at halftime, and used an 11-1 run in the second half to take a 50-36 lead with 12:18 remaining. North Texas shot 61.1 percent from 3-point range (11-for-18).
